ce:section.ce:para:
In order to explore the chemical composition and functional group on the surface of CQDs. Firstly, the XPS analysis (Fig. 5
                        ) results were presented in the focused C 1s spectra of 20-CQDs, 30-CQDs and 40-CQDs. The spectra consist of peaks obtained by deconvolution: C=C (284.88 eV), C-O (286.5 eV) and -COOH (288 eV). From quantitative analysis (Table 1
                        .), it could be found that as reaction time arises from 20 min to 40 min, the percentage of C=C was decrease from 91.03% to 80.92. Meanwhile, C-O and -COOH increase from 4.05% to 11.1% and 4.92%–7.75%. The XPS results indicated that some C=C onto the surface of CQDs were oxidized to C-O and -COOH during reaction time.
